      "citation_id": "[CITATION_1]",
      "span_text": "Increasing the oleic acid content of milk fat from 26% to over 40% by feeding calcium salts of HOSO containing more than 86% oleic acid at the rate of 7.5% of diet dry matter weight to Holstein cows did not affect the sensory and physicochemical properties of Latin American white cheese (Queso Blanco). There was also no difference (as a result of the modified and improved fatty acid profile) between the firmness of the product from modified milk and that made from normal milk [CITATION_1] ."
